<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('../../partials/head') %>
<body class="bg-[#0F172A] text-slate-200 min-h-screen flex font-sans">
    <%- include('../../partials/sidebar') %>
    <main class="ml-64 flex-1 p-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-10">Got questions? We've got answers.</p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
            <details class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 group open:border-blue-500/50 transition">
                <summary class="font-bold text-white cursor-pointer text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
                    What is "Raising" an idea?
                    <i class="ri-arrow-down-s-line text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition"></i>
                </summary>
                <p class="text-slate-400 mt-4 leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-800 pt-4">
                    "Raising" is similar to an upvote or a "like" on other platforms. However, on Ideate, it signifies moreâ€”it means you see potential in the concept and want to see it built. Ideas with the most Raises appear on the "Hall of Fame".
                </p>
            </details>

            <details class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 group open:border-blue-500/50 transition">
                <summary class="font-bold text-white cursor-pointer text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
                    Is my intellectual property safe here?
                    <i class="ri-arrow-down-s-line text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition"></i>
                </summary>
                <p class="text-slate-400 mt-4 leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-800 pt-4">
                    Ideate is an open platform. While our community guidelines prohibit theft, <strong>we recommend not posting sensitive trade secrets or patent-pending mechanics</strong>. Share the "What" and "Why", but keep the proprietary "How" to yourself until you are protected.
                </p>
            </details>

            <details class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 group open:border-blue-500/50 transition">
                <summary class="font-bold text-white cursor-pointer text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
                    Can I collaborate with other users?
                    <i class="ri-arrow-down-s-line text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition"></i>
                </summary>
                <p class="text-slate-400 mt-4 leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-800 pt-4">
                    Absolutely! That's the whole point. You can use the comments section to offer help. In the future, we are launching a "Join Team" feature to formalize partnerships.
                </p>
            </details>

             <details class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 group open:border-blue-500/50 transition">
                <summary class="font-bold text-white cursor-pointer text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
                    How do I change my Profile Picture?
                    <i class="ri-arrow-down-s-line text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition"></i>
                </summary>
                <p class="text-slate-400 mt-4 leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-800 pt-4">
                    Go to <a href="/settings" class="text-blue-400 underline">Settings</a> via the sidebar or clicking your profile. Click on your current avatar to upload a new image. We support JPG and PNG formats up to 5MB.
                </p>
            </details>

            <details class="bg-slate-900 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 group open:border-blue-500/50 transition">
                <summary class="font-bold text-white cursor-pointer text-lg flex justify-between items-center">
                    Can I delete my account?
                    <i class="ri-arrow-down-s-line text-slate-500 group-open:rotate-180 transition"></i>
                </summary>
                <p class="text-slate-400 mt-4 leading-relaxed border-t border-slate-800 pt-4">
                    Yes. In the Settings page, scroll to the bottom "Danger Zone". Deleting your account is permanent and will remove all your posted ideas and comments.
                </p>
            </details>
        </div>
    </main>
</body>
</html>